A 'good quality data' refers to a quality flag of 0 in the data quality table; 
The average temperature is calculated based on temperature 1 (t1) in degrees Celsius; 
Seasons are categorized as follows: 1 = Spring, 2 = Summer, 3 = Autumn, 4 = Winter.

